  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to institutions that preserve and provide access to documentary heritage in Southern Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Documentary heritage constitutes a major part of the memory of the peoples of the world and reflects the diversity of peoples, languages and cultures. Southern Africa has very few inscriptions to the memory of the World international registry . Climate Change impact is also another threat for the region&apos;s documentary heritage, Not withstanding, the value that documentary heritage, especially that which relates to the liberation movement can contribute to peace education in the light of recent attacks (Xenophobic? Economic based attacks).This actions will contribute to promoting preservation, dissemination and use of documentary heritage in the region for peace strengthening and sustainable development</narrative>
  </description>
